The Ferrari of Charles Leclerc looked incredible during the first stint. While Perez did manage to overtake the Ferrari after the first round of stops, it looked certain for Charles to seal off the podium. Everything changed when the engine cut off on lap 41. This saw Sainz take over as the lead Ferrari. However, the race pace of the Ferrari was not enough to maintain P3 as Alonso managed to snatch the position on lap 45.Continue reading the full story on Double Apex...